rComments: Nice professor who cares for her students. Not amazing at teaching but tries her best to explain concepts and shows simple experiments in class to help with understanding. Her tests are easier than Harlows. Test questions are directly out of the textbook. If you do bad, it's because you didnt study. Do all 100+ questions  for each chapter for an A+

The course was just high school review, but I appreciated how Natalia did it in a rigorous way - it was challenging, but not too hard. Any first-year EngSci/Physics students, ask her about POPTOR! It's a lot of fun to volunteer for.
It's true that she does have a very strong accent but she makes herself clear and answers questions.  I find that her class is not difficult and that she is quite an adorable Russian  lady :)
She has the ability to make a simple concept appear difficult and answers a simple question with a difficult answer and overcomplicates things.
